                <h4 class='border-bottom'>Inadequate physical activity among elderly Australians</h4>
                <p class='pt-3'>Did you know? Only around 1 in 10 Australians aged over 50 is deemed to conduct enough exercise. This number further declines with the increase in age. ABS indicated 42% older adult aged 65 to 74 did no exercise, as the age increases, this figure drastically increased to almost 60% for people above age 75.</p>
